 winter: A biological model for impact events and related dark/cold climate changes (1999) Climatic Change, 41, pp. 151-173; Crawford, D.A., Comet Shoemaker-Levy 9 fragment size estimates: How big was the parent body? (1997) Ann. N. Y. Acad. Sci., 822, pp. 155-173; Crowley, T.J., Causes of climate change over the past 1000 years (2000) Science, 289, pp. 270-277; Crowley, T.J., Burke, K.C., (1998) Tectonic Boundary Conditions for Climate Reconstructions, , Oxford University Press, Oxford; Crutzen, P.J., Birks, J.W., The atmosphere after a nuclear war: Twilight at noon (1982) Ambio, 11, pp. 114-125; D'Arrigo, R., Frank, D., Jacoby, G., Pederson, N., Spatial response to major volcanic events in or about A.D. 536, 934 and 1258: Frost rings and other dendrochronological evidence from Mongolia and northern Siberia - Comment on R.B. Stothers, volcanic dry fogs, climate cooling and plague pandemics in Europe and the middle east (Climatic Change 42, 1999) (2001) Climatic Change, 49, pp. 239-246; Dansgaard, W., Johnsen, S.J., Clausen, H.B., Dahl-Jensen, D., Gundestrup, N.S., Hammer, C.U., Hvidberg, C.S., Bond, G., Evidence for the general instability of past climate from a 250-kyr ice-core record (1993) Nature, 364, pp. 218-220; DeMenocal, P.B., Cultural responses to climate change during the late holocene (2001) Science, 292, pp. 667-673; DeMenocal, P., Ortiz, J., Guilderson, T., Sarntheim, M., Coherent high- and low-latitude climate variability during the holocene warm period (2000) Science, 288, pp. 2198-2202; Denton, G.H., Karlen, W., Holocene climatic variations - Their pattern and possible cause (1973) Q. Res., 3, pp. 155-205; Eddy, J.A., The Maunder minimum. The reign of Louis XIV appears to have been a time of real anomaly in the behavior of the sun (1976) Science, 192, pp. 1189-1202; Ehrlich, P.R., Harte, J., Harwell, M.A., Raven, P.H., Sagan, C., Woodwell, G.M., Berry, J., Teal, J.M., Long-term biological consequences of nuclear war (1983) Science, 222, pp. 1293-130